name: Dennis M. Baldwin, MBA, CPM
title: City Manager
summary: City Manager | Former Consultant & Police Chief with 35 years of municipal government experience, including 15 years of experience providing strategic, senior executive leadership.

member_experience_collection.title: Consultant
member_experience_collection.description: I help management, or their representatives, solve problems related to operations, employees, or strategic planning through advice, support, and guidance.

member_experience_collection.title: Assistant City Manager (Interim)
member_experience_collection.description: I provided executive leadership and oversight to city departments, facilitated plan development and project management, and prepared studies and reports to facilitate decision-making.

member_experience_collection.title: Assistant City Manager
member_experience_collection.description: I provided day-to-day operational oversight and leadership to 13 city departments e.g., Legal, Finance, Communications, Human Resources, Information Technology, Fire & EMS, Public Works, Community Services, Planning & Development, Community Development, Police, Aviation, Municipal Court.

member_experience_collection.title: City Manager (Interim)
member_experience_collection.description: I served as the chief executive officer of the city and chief advisor to the City Council, including managing the operations of the city and carrying out the City Council's priorities and policies.

member_experience_collection.title: Chief of Police
member_experience_collection.description: I administered the activities of the police department consistent with local, sate, and federal laws, including state civil service. These activities required planning, directing, and coordinating all activities of the department for the protection and safety of the community. Other responsibilities included: strategic planning, budgeting, executive oversight to dignitary protection and special events, as well as complex criminal/internal investigations.

member_experience_collection.title: Police Officer
member_experience_collection.description: I served in various roles and responsibilities: assistant police chief, deputy chief of field operations, patrol division commander, lieutenant of internal affairs, watch commander, field training officer coordinator, criminal investigations division crimes against persons sergeant, youth services sergeant, patrol watch sergeant, organized crime division narcotics investigator, and patrol officer.

member_recommendations_collection.recommendation: “Dennis Baldwin has a personality that qualifies him to work with diversified staff. He has a proven track record of stability through many years of service with the city. His work ethic is of stellar quality. He has an excellent proven track record as a supervisor, as he has managed multiple level employee positions with the Killeen Police Department. As his department interfaced with other City Departments, he has demonstrated excellent communication skills.”

“Chief Baldwin is a tremendous asset to our community. His willingness to think outside the box has created many programs for successful partnership between the community and our law enforcement professionals. The City of Killeen is a challenging environment for crime fighting and the staff that Chief Baldwin has assembled is more than up to the task!”
